sentences: Marion Peck (born October 3, 1963 in Manila, the Philippines) is a pop surrealist painter based in the United States.
Marion Peck was born on October 3, 1963 in Manila, the Philippines, while her family was on a trip around the world.
Peck received a BFA from the Rhode Island School of Design in 1985.
On October 24, 2009, Peck married longtime partner Mark Ryden, also a pop surrealist in the woods of the Pacific Northwest Rainforest.

Subsequently, she studied in two different MFA programs: Syracuse University in New York and Temple University in Rome, after which she lived in Italy for a few years, absorbing art, landscape, and food.
